div.p:
When I came to one Paragraph, (which is a quotation out of ſome modern Jeſuit)
I proteſt I ſtood amazed to hear of a meritorious congruity as well as condignity;
Now where there can be no congruity, there ought to be condignity, that's moſt clear;
and therefore ſince we could not agree to make him Alderman of the Ward, 'tis fit
he ſhould tell us of it by the way of condignity. And ſo much for a meritorious congruity.
